## 3) Key Concepts

### 3.1 Handled Receipt
A standard, premium “receipt” for every completed job that includes:
- What service + Level was scheduled
- What service + Level was actually performed (if courtesy upgrade)
- Proof-of-work (photos + checklist completion)
- Notes and exceptions
- Issues raised and resolution status (if any)
- One-tap “next time” adjustments

### 3.2 Receipt-Driven Expansion (Tasteful)
Expansion surfaces only appear in contexts where they feel helpful:
- “To keep this standard, update to Level 3 next time (+5 handles)”
- “While we’re here next cycle, add inside windows (+X handles)”
Rules: few, relevant, skippable, not repeated aggressively.

