## 5) Customer Experience Requirements

## 5.1 Receipts list screen
**Screen:** Receipts (list)
- Filter by property (if multi-property supported)
- Filter by service category (optional v1)
- Each row shows:
  - service name
  - date/time
  - “Handled standard met” status
  - # photos
  - issues flag (if present)
  - Level label (e.g., “Level 2”)
  - Provider name/org (as allowed)

## 5.2 Receipt detail screen (core deliverable)
Receipt detail must show, in this order:

### Section A — Summary header
- Service name (SKU)
- Date/time
- Property
- Provider identity (name/org) + rating surface (optional)
- Status badge:
  - ✅ Completed — Handled Standard Met
  - ⚠️ Completed — Attention Needed (if proof missing or issue opened)

### Section B — Scope & Level block (trust + clarity)
- **Scheduled Level:** Level X (label + short description)
- If courtesy upgrade:
  - **Performed Level:** Level Y (Courtesy Upgrade)
  - Reason code (short)
- What’s included (collapsed bullets)
- What’s excluded (collapsed bullets)
- Time window (if available)

### Section C — Proof-of-work
- Photo gallery with required minimum counts shown:
  - “8/8 photos uploaded”
- Checklist completion:
  - show top-level checklist categories with completed counts
  - allow “view checklist” drill-in (optional v1)

### Section D — Notes & Exceptions
- Provider notes (short and structured)
- Customer-visible flags (“gate locked”, “dog in yard”, etc.)

### Section E — Issues / Support (if applicable)
- Issue status (open/in progress/resolved)
- Evidence attached
- Link to open support thread/ticket

### Section F — Next time (tasteful recommendation module)
Only show if there is a high-confidence, relevant recommendation.

Examples:
- **Level recommendation** from provider:
  - “Recommended next time: Level 3 (+5 handles)”
  - Reason: “Inside windows requested / many windows / 2 stories”
  - CTA: **Update going forward**
  - Alternative: “Keep current level” (with calm warning)
- **While we’re here next time** (adjacent add-on):
  - “Add screen cleaning next time (+X handles)”
  - CTA: **Add to next cycle**

Hard rule: max **2** items in this module.

