## 9) Data Model Requirements

### 9.1 Receipt representation (likely existing jobs table + proof tables)
Receipt is derived from:
- `jobs` (service date/time, sku_id, scheduled level, performed level)
- `job_proof_photos` (urls, types, timestamps)
- `job_checklist` (items, completion)
- `job_level_feedback` (sufficient, recommended level, reason code)
- `issues/disputes` (if any)

### 9.2 New tables (if needed)
#### `receipt_recommendations`
Store computed recommendations (so UI is deterministic):
- `id`
- `job_id`
- `type` (LEVEL_CHANGE / ADD_ADJACENT)
- `sku_id` (if add-on)
- `level_id` (if level change)
- `reason` (string)
- `handles_delta`
- `priority`
- `created_at`

#### `receipt_actions`
Track what the customer did:
- `id`
- `job_id`
- `action_type` (ACCEPT_RECOMMENDATION / DECLINE / HIDE)
- `payload` json
- `created_at`

